        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "value": "What is nvm? 🤔",
            "position": {
              "start": { "line": 2, "column": 3, "offset": 3 },
              "end": { "line": 2, "column": 18, "offset": 18 },
              "indent": []
            }
          }
        ],
        "position": {
          "start": { "line": 2, "column": 1, "offset": 1 },
          "end": { "line": 2, "column": 18, "offset": 18 },
          "indent": []
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "emphasis",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "value": "nvm is a version manager for node.js, designed to be installed per-user, and invoked per-shell. nvm works on any POSIX-compliant shell (sh, dash, ksh, zsh, bash), in particular on these platforms: unix, macOS, and windows WSL.",
                "position": {
                  "start": { "line": 4, "column": 2, "offset": 21 },
                  "end": { "line": 4, "column": 228, "offset": 247 },
                  "indent": []
                }
              }
            ],
            "position": {
              "start": { "line": 4, "column": 1, "offset": 20 },
              "end": { "line": 4, "column": 229, "offset": 248 },
              "indent": []
            }
          }
        ],
        "position": {
          "start": { "line": 4, "column": 1, "offset": 20 },
          "end": { "line": 4, "column": 229, "offset": 248 },
          "indent": []
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "depth": 1,
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "value": "Why should I use nvm? 🤔",
            "position": {
              "start": { "line": 6, "column": 3, "offset": 252 },
              "end": { "line": 6, "column": 27, "offset": 276 },
              "indent": []
            }
          }
        ],
        "position": {
          "start": { "line": 6, "column": 1, "offset": 250 },
          "end": { "line": 6, "column": 27, "offset": 276 },
          "indent": []
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "value": "If you're developing software using the NodeJS runtime environment you're probably aware that you might want have multiple projects using different node versions, say one using 10 and another 12. This could be due to a number of reasons. It gets annoying switching between node versions manually.",
            "position": {
              "start": { "line": 8, "column": 1, "offset": 278 },
              "end": { "line": 8, "column": 297, "offset": 574 },
              "indent": []
            }
          }
        ],
        "position": {
          "start": { "line": 8, "column": 1, "offset": 278 },
          "end": { "line": 8, "column": 297, "offset": 574 },
          "indent": []
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "depth": 1,
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "value": "Manual usage of nvm 🐌",
            "position": {
              "start": { "line": 10, "column": 3, "offset": 578 },
              "end": { "line": 10, "column": 25, "offset": 600 },
              "indent": []
            }
          }
        ],
        "position": {
          "start": { "line": 10, "column": 1, "offset": 576 },
          "end": { "line": 10, "column": 25, "offset": 600 },
          "indent": []
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "value": "The project nvm solves this problem by allowing the user to install node versions on the fly by using a simple command:",
            "position": {
              "start": { "line": 12, "column": 1, "offset": 602 },
              "end": { "line": 12, "column": 120, "offset": 721 },
              "indent": []
            }
          }
        ],
        "position": {
          "start": { "line": 12, "column": 1, "offset": 602 },
          "end": { "line": 12, "column": 120, "offset": 721 },
          "indent": []
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "html",
        "lang": null,
        "meta": null,
        "value": "<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">nvm install &lt;NODE_VERSION_NUMBER&gt;</code></pre></div>",
        "position": {
          "start": { "line": 14, "column": 1, "offset": 723 },
          "end": { "line": 16, "column": 4, "offset": 764 },
          "indent": [1, 1]
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "value": "You can also easily switch between node versions using a simple command:",
            "position": {
              "start": { "line": 18, "column": 1, "offset": 766 },
              "end": { "line": 18, "column": 73, "offset": 838 },
              "indent": []
            }
          }
        ],
        "position": {
          "start": { "line": 18, "column": 1, "offset": 766 },
          "end": { "line": 18, "column": 73, "offset": 838 },
          "indent": []
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "html",
        "lang": null,
        "meta": null,
        "value": "<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">nvm use &lt;NODE_VERSION_NUMBER&gt;</code></pre></div>",
        "position": {
          "start": { "line": 20, "column": 1, "offset": 840 },
          "end": { "line": 22, "column": 4, "offset": 877 },
          "indent": [1, 1]
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "depth": 1,
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "value": "Automated usage of nvm 🤖",
            "position": {
              "start": { "line": 24, "column": 3, "offset": 881 },
              "end": { "line": 24, "column": 28, "offset": 906 },
              "indent": []
            }
          }
        ],
        "position": {
          "start": { "line": 24, "column": 1, "offset": 879 },
          "end": { "line": 24, "column": 28, "offset": 906 },
          "indent": []
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "value": "Let's face it, you're going to forget to switch to the correct node version at some point.",
            "position": {
              "start": { "line": 26, "column": 1, "offset": 908 },
              "end": { "line": 26, "column": 91, "offset": 998 },
              "indent": []
            }
          }
        ],
        "position": {
          "start": { "line": 26, "column": 1, "offset": 908 },
          "end": { "line": 26, "column": 91, "offset": 998 },
          "indent": []
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "value": "We can in a sense, automate the switching between versions.",
            "position": {
              "start": { "line": 28, "column": 1, "offset": 1000 },
              "end": { "line": 28, "column": 60, "offset": 1059 },
              "indent": []
            }
          }
        ],
        "position": {
          "start": { "line": 28, "column": 1, "offset": 1000 },
          "end": { "line": 28, "column": 60, "offset": 1059 },
          "indent": []
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "value": "It's a simple solution which only requires a one-time setup:",
            "position": {
              "start": { "line": 30, "column": 1, "offset": 1061 },
              "end": { "line": 30, "column": 61, "offset": 1121 },
              "indent": []
            }
          }
        ],
        "position": {
          "start": { "line": 30, "column": 1, "offset": 1061 },
